{
  "local_port": 44366,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "Checking your **Provident Fund (PF)** balance is a straightforward process, and there are multiple ways to do it. Here are the most common methods:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Using the EPFO Portal (Online Method)**  \n**Steps:**  \n1. **Visit the EPFO Portal**: Go to [https://www.epfindia.gov.in](https://www.epfindia.gov.in).  \n2. **Login to Your Account**:\n   - If you are a registered user, log in using your UAN and password.\n   - If you are not registered, click on **\"For Employees\"** > **\"Member UAN/Online Services (OCS/OTCP)\"** and activate your UAN.\n3. **Check Your Balance**:\n   - After logging in, go to **\"View Passbook\"** under the **\"Services\"** tab.\n   - Your PF balance and transaction details will be displayed.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Via UMANG App (Mobile Method)**  \n**Steps:**  \n1. **Download the UMANG App**: Available on Google Play Store or Apple App Store.  \n2. **Log In or Register**: Use your mobile number or Aadhaar to log in.  \n3. **Select EPFO Services**:\n   - Search for \"EPFO\" in the app.\n   - Choose **\"View Passbook\"**.\n4. **Enter Your UAN**: Log in with your UAN and view your PF balance.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Through SMS (Without Internet)**  \n**Steps:**  \n1. **Ensure Your UAN is Linked to Your Mobile Number**: Your UAN must be activated and linked to your mobile number.  \n2. **Send an SMS**: Type **EPFOHO UAN ENG** and send it to **7738299899**.  \n3. **Receive Your Balance**: You will receive an SMS with your PF balance.  \n   - Replace **ENG** with your preferred language code (e.g., HIN for Hindi).\n\n---\n\n### **4. Via Missed Call Service**  \n**Steps:**  \n1. **Ensure Your UAN is Linked to Your Mobile Number**.  \n2. **Give a Missed Call**: Dial **011-22901406** from your registered mobile number.  \n3. **Receive Your Balance**: You will receive an SMS with your PF balance.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Through EPFO Mobile App**  \n**Steps:**  \n1. **Download the EPFO App**: Available on Google Play Store or Apple App Store.  \n2. **Log In**: Use your UAN and password to log in.  \n3. **Check Your Balance**: Navigate to **\"View Passbook\"** to see your PF balance.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Offline Method (EPFO Office)**  \nIf you are unable to check your balance online, you can visit your nearest **EPFO office** with your UAN and identity proof to request your PF balance.\n\n---\n\n### **Requirements to Check PF Balance Online**  \n1. **UAN (Universal Account Number)**: Must be activated.  \n2. **Mobile Number**: Linked to your UAN.  \n3. **Internet Access**: For online methods (EPFO portal, UMANG app, etc.).\n\nIf your UAN is not activated or linked to your mobile number, contact your employer or use the **EPFO portal** to activate it.\n\n---\n\nBy following any of the above methods, you can easily check your PF balance and stay updated on your contributions.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
